      "description": "Available now is an investment-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, featuring the masterfully engineered 13B-REW rotary engine. This example maintains its original sequential twin-turbocharger configuration, providing a seamless boost transition throughout the rev range. The powertrain is complemented by a crisp 5-speed manual transmission and a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal torque distribution. The chassis is impeccably preserved, retaining its factory-spec double-wishbone suspension and 50/50 weight distribution for unparalleled lateral grip and feedback. Compression tests yield consistent, high-range results across all rotor faces, and the cooling system has been meticulously maintained to prevent heat soak. Finished in original factory paint with a flawless interior, this is a rare, unmolested specimen of 90s Japanese engineering excellence.",
